def: An inhabitant or resident; -- a name applied to and denotingfarmers of French descent or origin in Canada, especially in theProvince of Quebec; -- usually in plural.The habitants or cultivators of the soil. Parkman.
Divination by the ashes of the altar on which a victim had beenconsumed in sacrifice.
An instrument for measuring the volumes of gases or liquids byintroducing them into a vessel of known capacity.
A measure of land in India, varying from a third of an acre toan acre.
Having colors like those of the rainbow; iridescent. Holmes.
